sp.p:
 
I hope I moved you not, but in fair language sir;  
Nor spoke a syllable that might offend you.  
 
 

 
 
I have not used the word of loan, or borrowing;  
Only some private conference I requested.

You shall be Judge Sir Hugh, whether I be defective; you have lain here Sir Hugh these three 
years, have been our constant lodger off and on as we say; 
and can you think me defective?

 
For which you shall have best instructions;  
You will run a chargeable course in it, 
that I will tell you:  And may yet if you please retain your money;  
Cross your mothers will and die a Clown.

I value neither shame, nor name, nor fame;  
And wealth I have none to lose; you have enough  
  To pay for all I take it.

You have a Nephew, whose sister I married, a virtuous wife she is, and I love him the better 
for it; he is a younger brother, and born to no great fortune: 
now you are very rich, a Bachelor, and therefore I think childlesse ---

 
I commend your worldly providence;  
Madam, such good Ladies will never dance  
Away their husbands Lands.

No, no, I know her, it is Mistress. Holy-hocke the precise Drapers wife; 
O, how my longing grows stronger in me: I see what shift soever a woman makes with her husband 
at home, a friend does best abroad.

    Yes Hoyden, so I say; there be very good folks of the name, as you shall well know; 
I cham one myself, and she need not be ashamed I wuss of 
the kin she came on, to hugger mugger it as she did to her dying day.

 
Ugh, ugh, no Fid ugh hem! he has cured me:  
I am light at heart again: he has cured me;  
He has played the good Physician against his will;  
And a halter be his fee for it.

No sir, we come with no sick intendment on neither neither side; but 
if you be Master. Striker, we are on your side, 
an it be to cut all the rest into Pot herbs.

 
I come to cry you mercy, and this good gentleman;  
And this sweet Gentlewoman, who I take it  
Is his fair Niece, of whom you are in treaty;  
If it be not already gone too far;  
Let me entreat you not to put your finger  
Further in the business in behalf of your Nephew.

For that my letter of instructions, which I have given Annabell shall prevent him; 
and Striker keeps Sir Cautious in his house so warily that until the intended wedding hour, 
Sir. Hugh shall not obtain admittance.

 
And dressed, and dressed indeed;  
Never was maid so dressed: O sir you are happy;  
The happiest Knight, and are now in election  
Of the most sweet encounter in a bride,  
That ever your chivalry could couch a Lance at.

 
To you I need not; for you know it already;  
But to my friend Sir Cautious, whom I honour,  
And would not see so shipwrecked, I may speak it.

 
I come not as a guest sir, or spectator  
To your great wedding, but on the Kings affairs;  
In which I must crave your assistance sir;  
Deny it me, or my entrance, if you dare.

And a gentleman? what a devilish deal of money might I have saved! 
for gentlemen let me tell you, I have been cozened black and blue; back gulled and belly gulled, 
and have nothing left me but a little bare Complement to live upon, as I am a clear gentleman.

The Stocks were fitter for him: the most corrupted fellow  

 
 

 

about the Suburbs, his conscience is stewed in Bribes, all his poor neighbours curse him; 
it is though the keeps a whore now at threescore.
